body:
Added GetProfilePicture, SetProfilePicture and fixed MessageImage.

Added WhatsMediaUploader class (required for MessageImage())

Added error suppression (@) to socket_read() in readData(), the cause of many issue reports

Automatically downloads received media images to /src/php/media.

Added GetJID($to) method which will always return a JID. This is to prevent accidental use of number instead of JID, or adding whatsAppServer twice to a target which is already a JID.

Also added some minor fixes after looking in the issue tracker and added a number of methods from WhatsApiNet.

Updated testprotocol.php with SetProfilePicture and MessageImage

commit.message: Fixes issue of Accessing static property WhatsApEvent::$event_callbacks as non static
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI.git

Fixed typo

Issue 314
https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI/issues/314

Optional nickname

Made nickname optional, Issue 301
https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI/issues/301

Prevent confirming messages to yourself

Issue 293:
https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI/issues/293

Automatic JID conversion and several new methods

Hopefully got rid of the long standing issue of using numbers instead of
JIDs. This method will always output a JID whether you enter a number or
a JID.
Added several methods taken from WhatsApiNet (C#)

Added GetProfilePicture

Added GetProfilePicture: fetches profile picture and stores it in
pictures/[JID].jpg
for some reason only thumbnails work at the moment, need to look into
this.

Fixed SendPresence() sending empty name attribute when no nickname was
provided, resulted in xml error protocolnode.

Included GetProfilePicture() output folder

Added placeholder in /src/php/pictures in order to add output folder to
repository

Updated testprotocol.php

Added GetProfilePicture() to retrieve large profile picture, fore some
reason it magically started working again :o
Replaced five Message() calls with just one to protect user from being
blocked.

Reverted changes to Nickname

Nickname mandatory again, resulted in xmlformatting errors.

Added support for both profile pictures

Large profile pictures are stored as "[JID].jpg" and previews as
"preview_[JID].jpg"

Added support for receiving images

When receiving an image it will be downloaded in /src/php/media. It
saves the included thumbnail and downloads the original image by its
URL.

Added placeholder file for /src/php/media in order to include it in the
repository.

Added SetProfilePicture

Enables you to change your profile picture. Example included in
testprotocol.php as well as a demo profile picture in /src/php/media.
AFAIK only JPEG is allowed.

Added WhatsMediaUploader class

Added class to upload images to whatsapp using the updated protocol.

https://github.com/tgalal/yowsup/commit/f586ead9ebec89b841ec736f0dc330b06a7f8917

Fixed sending images

Fixed image file upload/request/send.
Added sending demo image to testprotocol.php

Updated socket handling

Changed socket calls from socket_*() to fread() and fwrite() to simplify
things (saved one line of code!) and made the socket persistent. This
"should" enable using AJAX calls to send and receive messages without
the need to log in for each AJAX call (still have to test it).

Added AJAX chat example

Added simple AJAX chat example to /src/php/ajaxDemo.
You have to enter the contact phonenumber in index.php, and your
credentials in socket.php.
Start the demo by going to index.php.
This will start a socket listener process in the background. This
process will pull and push messages to and from the $_SESSION variable.
The queues for inbound and outbound messages are stored in the $_SESSION
global variable.
At this time only sending and receiving text messages to and from a
single contact is supported.
I plan to add contact picture, composing status and message delivery
status to this example. If there is enough interest I might also create
a new repository focused on this :)
Now excuse me while I'll try to get some sleep, been up all night, it's
6:21 AM :")

Added onProfilePicture event

Added onProfilePicture event so the user can decide for himself how he
wants to handle the received profile picture.
Also added PollMessages() to SendMessageNode() and sendStatusUpdate() to
ensure delivery.

Updated ajaxDemo

Added contact's profile picture to conversation demo.
http://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/68235039/whatsapiajax.png

Added image support in ajaxDemo

AjaxDemo automatically downloads and displays received images.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/shirioko/WhatsAPI.git into pollmessagefix

Added new WaitforServer() function to ensure server has received and responded to sending messages/updating status etc.

This is NOT the same as waiting for a delivery receipt. The other handset could be offline and so you may not receive that notification for hours...

Merge pull request #1 from jonnywilliamson/master

Create a waitforserver function to ensure request is processed

Fixed Disconnect() method

Changed from socket to file handler.

Removed error message on read error

Proper error check and handling to be implemented.
Now able to send Image/Video/Audio messages from both local file AND an URL.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/shirioko/WhatsAPI.git into pollmessagefix

Merge pull request #2 from jonnywilliamson/master

Ability to send Audio/Video/Image messages via URL or local file.

Fixed reconnection

See issue 321:
https://github.com/venomous0x/WhatsAPI/issues/321
Moved construction of reader and writer from __construct() to Connect()
to allow reconnection using the same WhatsProt object.

Cleaner reconnection fix

Moved the constructors for reader and writer back to __construct() and
added resetKey() method on new login request.

Disabled Login()

Too many questions about the same issue.
Fixed identity in requestCode()

Fix for reset key

`unset($this->_key);` will display `Notice: Undefined property`

Merge pull request #3 from atans/master

Fix for reset key

Removed my exception in checkCredentials

According to manufuentescr checkCredentials() still works, so no reason to disable it

Update WhatsProt::createGroupChat()

Param $participants is an option now

Merge pull request #4 from atans/patch-1

Update WhatsProt::createGroupChat()
Variable's first letter should be lowercase.

Merge pull request #5 from atans/patch-2

Variable's first letter should be lowercase.

Updated contacts.php

Automatically add leading "+" sign if necessary, this also means that
all phone numbers must now include country code. This is due to many
questions about it and having the documentation hidden in the php file
instead of the wiki.
Added debug to contact sync

Disabled verbose mode in contacts.php

Thanks to @manufuentescr
Updated contacts.php

Added support for custom identity

Allows you to enter a custom identity on Login()
This identity can be extracted from your phone using either MissVenom or
WhatSNiff

Added debug info to checkCredentials

Added debug info since there were many questions about it.

Added thumbnails using GD

Added thumbnails for sending image messages using the GD extension.
Previously this only worked using the ImageMagic extension which is
quite uncommon.

requestCode debug and error handling

Added debug info and improved error handling in WhatsProt::requestCode()
Fixed typo causing warnings
Fixed icon generation using imagick. Surprised this is an uncommon setup(!)

Merge pull request #6 from jonnywilliamson/master

Small fix for icon generation for imagick

Video fixes

Changes file size limit to 20MB and now setting the proper file type on
upload response
Deleted unused python code
Fixed icon generation
Add videothumbnail
Add Videothumbnail call.

Added and verified all approved media file types.
Changed max file size (Mb) for each media type to an easy to set number if user needs to change. Currently 5Mb for Images, 10Mb for Audio and 20Mb for Video.

Merge pull request #7 from jonnywilliamson/master

New videothumbnail and updated approved media file types.

Add ability to retrieve all groups user belongs to. 
Defaults to "participating" in a group, but can be set to show only the "owning" groups.

Merge pull request #8 from jonnywilliamson/master

GetGroupList Implemented.

Added contact sync page

Back by popular demand!
Some formatting fixes

Added message broadcast

Y U NO STAR ME??? :'(

title: Many image related fixes
